# {{plural of|orthopaedist|lang=en}}.
Orthopedist is so called from Greek root orthos, means  straight or correct, and paidos, mean child. 

The term was coined in 1741 by an author of a book on the prevention of childhood diseases -at that time children were having problems of deformation of bones, injuries joints. So this expert do correct's the bones,joints by surgery (not only children but adults also)
Adjective is orthopeadic.